==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crofton system
<hw>Crof"ton sys"tem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[After <person>Sir Walter
<etsep>Crofton</etsep></person>, Irish penologist.]</ety>
<fld>(Penology)</fld> <def>A system of prison discipline employing for
consecutive periods cellular confinement, associated imprisonment under
the mark system, restraint intermediate between imprisonment and
freedom, and liberation on ticket of leave.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crois</ent>⟦br⟧
